The simple answer is, no Many companies consistently struggle with inventory management, whether it be SKUS out of stock dated, or systems not communicating with one Traditionally, this would leave people with no options but to manually handle tasks such as pulling inventory from different systems or vendors, and consolidating it by hand to see what they currently have in â Inevitable problems Doing such a high volume task like this will inevitably lead to We aren t saying you don t do a good job, we re saying statistically the error rate of humans & inefficiencies of doing it with a person far outweigh the benefits of actually doing the task, so this can many times lead to the task not being done (hence supply chain problems you always hear of). â The solution We saw this problem from far away, and have been able to consistently solve it for many of our clients by utilizing technology known as "bots" that can mimic human behavior for high volume tasks (not to mention, they re more efficient). Below is a debriefing of one of our use cases in which we were able to reduce the estimated time spent of 4 months to get the task done, to 4 hours when done by a This use case specifically is regarding a company that was looking to update ,000 products on a monthly basis from an external source to their internal system, allowing them to consistently have new pictures, description, updated pricing, and inventory counts (among other things as well). â written by Cory Shreffler share on Similar posts Read on :) Cory Shreffler Inventory Management How this company reduced 4 months of work to 4 hours October , 5 Hate it?Â Let s Automate It! CENTERED AT OUR CORE In , an act of Congress authorized a federal district along the Potomac River, situated at the boundary of northern and southern states, and offering easy inland passage to the western President Washington asked Pierre L’Enfant, an emigrant from France who had fought alongside colonial soldiers in the Revolutionary War, to formulate a design of the “Federal City”. With the assistance of Andrew Ellicott, who helped map the western frontier, and Benjamin Banneker, a free surveyor and astronomer, the plans for what is now Washington were A core element of their grand design was the “Capitol Meridian”, a line traversing the heart of what would later become the Capi

Corporate Transparency Act - FinCen New Filing requirements Skip to content Home Blog Contact us About FinCEN Search for: Home » Corporate Transparency Act Corporate Transparency Act ken :04:36+00:00 Corporate Transparency Act As part of the National Defense Authorization Act of Congress adopted the Corporate Transparency Act (or “CTA”). The CTA includes some of the most significant changes to US laundering (“AML”) laws in recent One of the primary changes requires the beneficial owners of corporations, partnerships, limited liability companies and other businesses to file a report that discloses their beneficial This will have a significant impact on entrepreneurs, business owners, attorneys and others involved in forming new The government uses AML to identify parties involved in money Before the CTA it was possible to form a corporation, partnership or limited liability company without publicly disclosing the owners of the The CTA will end that The CTI will compel the beneficial owners of most businesses to register their beneficial ownership with FinCEN, the Financial Crime Enforcement Network, an agency of the Treasury The CTA requires the Treasury Department to issue regulations to implement this new New covered entities must report their beneficial ownership within fourteen days after they are Entities that existed before the effective date of the new regulations will have one year to identify their beneficial The CTA defines “beneficial owner” to include any individual, directly or indirectly, through any contract, arrangement, understanding, relationship or otherwise who: Exercises substantial control over the covered entity, or Holds at least percent of the ownership interests of the covered Importantly, the CTA does not define “substantial control” and does not describe how ownership interests are to be We expect that the upcoming FinCEN regulations will define these The CTA provides several exemptions that apply to specific categories of beneficial ownership: Custodians agents for an individual, or those acting solely as an employee of an An entity’s creditors, unless the creditor holds at least percent of the ownership interests of the covered entity or substantial An individual whose only interest in a covered entity is through a “right of ” A minor child if the information of the parent (or guardian) is The obligation to file a FinCEN report is an obligation of the covered entity The covered entity must report, for each beneficial owner, as well as the individual that files the paperwork to form or register an entity with a state secretary of state or similar office: Full legal name, Date of birth, Current residential or business street address, and A unique identifying number from an acceptable identity document or a unique identity number generated by Importantly, if an exempt entity has a direct or indirect ownership in a covered entity, the covered entity must report the legal name of the exempt entity, but not the other information generally The CTA exempts a variety of different entities from the obligation to file a FinCEN Most exempt entities are already subject to some form of federal regulation that gives federal law enforcement visibility into their Some of the key forms of exempt entities are: Public companies (defined as issuers of a class of securities under section of the Securities Exchange Act of or issuers that are required to file information under section (d) of that Act). Any entity that employs more than employees in the United States, filed a federal tax return for the previous year with more than $5 million in gross receipts or sales (includes subsidiaries and operating affiliates), and operates from a physical US Shelf companies (defined as any entity that is in existence for over one year, not engaged in “active business,” and not directly or indirectly owned by a person). Skip to content Qui est Na#Dièse ? Mes créations Menu Fermer Qui est Na#Dièse ? Mes créations Qui est Na#Dièse ? Photo réalisée par Marjolaine Courbière, Photographe Nadiège Bordas, une créatrice atypique J’ai toujours su que j’étais Déjà par mon prénom : ce « i » intrigue toujours 🙂 mais il a toute sa place, et j’ai toujours fait attention à ce qu’il ne soit pas Il fait en effet partie de moi et de mon Différente aussi par l’intensité de mes Cette faculté de me mettre à la place de l’autre et de percevoir ce qu’il Le fait d’être submergée par l’émotion en observant la beauté de la Mais aussi d’être emportée par l’inspiration lorsqu’elle vient à moi à tout moment,…. Sensible et authentique, j’ai souvent souffert de l’intensité de mes ressentis, jusqu’au jour où j’ai pu les identifier : Hypersensibilité . Ce n’est que récemment que j’ai compris que ce trait de personnalité n’est pas un fardeau ni une faiblesse, mais au contraire un don et une véritable Mes passions, ce qui m anime Passionnée et intuitive, ma créativité s’est exprimée très A travers la musique depuis toujours : le chant depuis que je sais parler, puis en tant qu’auteur-compositeur-interprète depuis mon Elle s’est également exprimée à travers la pâtisserie , que m’a enseignée mon papa, pâtissier de Depuis une dizaine d’années, elle s’est affirmée tant au niveau de la création que de la technique : dans le motion design , le web , le graphisme , l’ infographie . Ma reconversion, une évidence Après plus de ans d’assistanat de direction, j’ai eu besoin de retrouver du sens à mon activité professionnelle, j’ai donc décidé de relier mes passions à ma C’est alors que le Digital est apparu pour moi comme une évidence : toujours accompagner les personnes, mais cette fois en liant relation à l’ Autre , créativité et technique : la meilleure des recettes ! Motion Designer certifiée , Créatrice en Communication Digitale, je suis désormais au diapason avec et mets mon empathie, mes compétences et ma technique au service de mes intuitions, pour VOUS ! Un accompagnement sur mesure Avant toute création, j’ai besoin de vous En présentiel ou en distanciel, nous échangeons sur votre projet, mais nous parlons également de vous : qui vous êtes, ce que vous aimez et n’aimez pas, ce qui vous anime,…. en résumé, nous créons un lien qui me connectera à vous ! Une construction main dans la main A la suite de cet échange et de la validation de ma proposition financière, je mets en commun mes ressentis issus de notre échange, et ce que ma créativité m’inspire. Pour une vidéo en Motion Design, un site internet, ou toute création graphique, à chaque étape je vous fais valider mon travail, afin de vous laisser la liberté d’ajuster mes Pour un logo, afin d’affiner ma création, je vous pose des questions si besoin, mais je vous réserve la surprise de la découverte ! Votre activité en toute sérénité Une fois le projet terminé, je continuerai à vous suivre en support si besoin, notamment pour un site Mon offre web inclut en effet une formation afin de pleinement vous approprier votre site : ajout de photos, articles de blog, gestion d’une boutique en ligne,…. et un contrat de Ainsi vous n’aurez à vous soucier de rien et pourrez vous consacrer pleinement à votre Valorisez votre différence ! Le monde du Digital évolue et nous devons évoluer avec lui, mais n’oublions pas de rester authentiques et fidèles à et à nos Une création unique vous rendra unique et valorisera votre entreprise

and BBDO on marketing campaigns for American Airlines, Southland Corporations (7-Eleven Stores) and to name a With over years of advertising, marketing and sales experience, Bell has a proven track includes live video replay and Hitrax, the first and only baseball Furthermore, a new fully equipped weight room has been added to the Billy Hebert Stadium, the two auxiliary fields and batting cages are all available for “We are so glad to have Bell Advertising on our team,” Hardcastle said, “I played on this field in college and it also plays such an important role in our Stockton history, so I am excited to see the rebirth of the field for more generations to ” In , Billy Hebert Field Baseball Complex hosted tournaments throughout the year and saw travel baseball teams and around 7,000 players coming from both Southern and Northern The Billy Hebert Field Baseball Complex is listed on the Northern California Travel Ball, NCTB, website along with the dates and registration information of upcoming Local Stockton charter high schools utilize the complex for many of their home The prestigious local travel ball team Club All Star, along with Delta College Baseball Team, currently train at the Billy Hebert Field Baseball Distinguished Club All Star alumni include Aaron Judge, Dean Kremer, Barry Enright and more who have all made it to the For more information on the Billy Hebert Misunderstanding Medical Translation: Why aren t we connecting? MEDICAL TRANSLATION Home Blog More Use tab to navigate through the menu All Posts Search Log in Sign up drjenhole Jul , 2 min read Misunderstanding Medical Translation: Why aren t we connecting? Updated: Jan 7 As the daughter of an immigrant, I witnessed the many hardships that occur when you are not a native English I watched my mother and grandmother struggle with disadvantage in not only the job and education market, but also when seeking the equivalent healthcare they were entitled Despite paying the same premium for their health insurance that many native English speakers paid, the quality of treatment and service they received was I learned growing up, that there are two healthcare systems in the United States, and that despite no official language - quality care was only delivered in Throughout my childhood I remember watching my grandmother, who moved to the US and learned English at the age of , battle breast cancer, During the course of treatment she had questions and concerns, but never had the tools available to actually connect with her The language barrier between herself and her Doctor left her scared and confused, yet she had no other option but to continue seeking less informed Carrying these experiences with me into adulthood, I was inspired to go into healthcare and be a part of the I desired to help create a world where equitable healthcare was practiced and not just discussed - where people were I envisioned a system where speakers thrived instead of just survived - A system where providers and patients When I look back on my ten years in practice as a Doctor, experiences have helped me to realize that the divide in the healthcare space is greater than ever The problem of care is not just a reality for my grandmother, but for the million Limited English Proficiency (LEP) patients in America My time in practice has been riddled with communication issues that have no great solution for encounters, and the most accessible options offer marginal results at Providers have been indoctrinated to become comfortable with inefficient or inaccurate translation solutions, leading patients to be forced into accepting a lessened experience service. What would truly ensure an LEP patient’s best interest? What would give providers confidence that communication on both sides is accurate? What kind of solution would build trust ? The healthcare space was built on the foundational pillars of , yet has it evolved into a system that readily accepts inequity? Our machines offer: Credit debit card reader in addition to taking cash and coins Daily remote monitoring so we know if a product selection is running low mode can be used so no power is wasted keeping drinks cold overnight if no employees are working Ability to program machine to provide employee discounts (e.g. to reward employees working on weekends) SmartCard technology – we can upload change machine settings quickly Capability to add Entrée Side Dish Vendor to machine for healthy meal options Machines are compliant with the American’s With Disabilities Act (ADA) guidelines for vending machines Machines are proudly made in the USA Does our company have to pay for the machine? Not a Machines are provided at absolutely NO cost to your In fact, not only do we provide the machine, we service and stock it on a regular Who stocks the machine? We We will monitor, stock and service the machine as often is Each of our operators are well trained to ensure that the quality of service provided is far superior to anything you may have experienced before with other We are local residents of your community and are therefore eager to share our commitment to offering healthy products to your employees customers. Can our company choose the products that go into the machine? Yes – your company can be instrumental in the products that are We believe it is important to provide a good variety of healthy products in order to satisfy We will initially fill the machine with the most popular healthy products selling in our Later, we will meet with you to discuss changes to the selections and your suggestions – and may offer some free product sampling events as How often is the machine stocked? Typically, about once a Each machine is equipped with wireless remote monitoring technology so we know if a product selection is running If it is determined that it needs to be serviced more often than once each week, we can set up a more frequent service What training have you received? We have gone through extensive training in several areas – including the operation and maintenance of the machine, nutritional guidelines, product management, inventory control, product sampling, But the main thing is customer service – we are here to serve you and the patrons of the We will provide you with a business card and a label on the machine with our local contact information should you ever need How many machines can you provide to our business – more than one? This depends on several First we need to evaluate the volume of foot traffic on a daily Next, we need to consider if there is competition from other vending machines located in your business if you have If these two factors confirm there’s enough demand for an additional machine, we will be happy to supply one to your Some locations such as large schools, businesses, colleges, may have enough demand for multiple What types of healthy products will be stocked in the machines? The healthy products we provide are all national name brand These are the same products you can find on the shelves of your local health food grocers such as Whole Foods, Trader Joes, Many of these healthier products are now going mainstream and can be found on the shelves of traditional grocery stores and even convenience Not only do the products we offer provide healthier alternatives, but they also taste great and people really love eating them! If we have a contract with another vendor, can we still receive a healthy vending machine? This depends on the specific Many contracts are exclusive only to “traditional” vending products (e.g. Snickers, Coke, ). Therefore, this doesn’t cause an issue as we can create menu plans of items to those in a different The reality is that many vending companies claim they can provide healthier options, but very few Do we have to sign an agreement? LASIK surgery is a laser vision correction procedure that permanently alters the shape of the By reshaping the cornea, your LASIK surgeon allows light to reflect properly onto the retina (the patch of tissue at the back of the eye). This means clear vision! LASIK is a safe, quick and effective way to improve your vision with little to no dependence on glasses and contact If you are frustrated with the constant maintenance, costs and inconvenience of glasses and contact lenses, LASIK may be for While not everyone is a candidate for LASIK surgery, the millions of people who have undergone the procedure swear by The short recovery makes it great for people with active, hectic lifestyles who need to get back to work Waking up in the morning with clear, crisp vision alone makes the LASIK procedure worth it! Am I a Candidate for LASIK? Are you at least years old? LASIK is best suited for adults with consistent vision While some patients are able to get LASIK at age under the right circumstances, we generally advise against The younger you are when you get LASIK, the more likely you are to need an enhancement surgery later on when your eyes grow and Is your cornea the right thickness? A simple test will reveal if your cornea is thick enough for LASIK If your cornea is too thin, you are at higher risk of LASIK In these cases, we will recommend a vision correction procedure more suited to your More Candidacy Considerations‍ After Cataract Surgery For Presbyopia With Astigmatism Find Out If You re a Candidate Benefits of LASIK Patients who undergo LASIK surgery experience not only improved eyesight , but also a number of secondary benefits which can lead to an overall higher quality of LASIK surgery allows you to see the world around you without the help of glasses and contact After LASIK surgery, you can expect to experience increased independence, improved , and even Benefits of LASIK Your LASIK Experience What to expect before, during, and after the Explore the entire timeline from consultation to clear Interested in LASIK but not sure what to expect?
